{
  "id": "nobody-knows-you",
  "title": "Nobody Knows You When You're Down and Out",
  "genres": ["blues"],
  "difficulty": "Developing",
  "key": "C",
  "chords": ["C", "E7", "A7", "Dm", "F", "D7", "G7"],
  "attribution": "Jimmie Cox, 1923",
  "lines": [
    "[section:Verse 1]",
    "[C]Once I lived the [E7]life of a [A7]millionaire",
    "[Dm]Spending my money, [A7]I didn't care",
    "[Dm]Taking my friends out [A7]for a mighty good time",
    "[D7]Buying bootleg liquor, [G7]champagne and wine",
    "",
    "[section:Verse 2]",
    "[C]Then I began to [E7]fall so [A7]low",
    "[Dm]Lost all my good friends, [A7]had nowhere to go",
    "[Dm]If I ever get my [A7]hands on a dollar again",
    "I'm gonna [D7]hold on to it till that [G7]eagle grins",
    "",
    "[section:Chorus]",
    "[C]Nobody [E7]knows you [A7]when you're down and [Dm]out",
    "[A7]In your pocket, [Dm]not one [A7]penny",
    "[Dm]And as for friends, [A7]you don't have any",
    "[D7]When you get back on your [G7]feet again",
    "[C]Everybody [E7]wants to [A7]be your long-lost [Dm]friend",
    "It's [D7]mighty strange, with[G7]out a [C]doubt"
  ],
